label("$x$",(3,0),S);
[/asy]

Since $PQ = QR,$ we have $QR = x.$ And since $PQ \times QR = 24,$ we have $x^2 = 24,$ or $x = 2\sqrt{6}.$ 

The area of the rectangle $PQRS$ is $PQ \times QR = x^2 = 24,$ so $PQ = QR = RS = SP = 2\sqrt{6}.$ 

 The area of quadrilateral $PTRS$ can be found by subtracting the area of right triangle $PQR$ from the area of trapezoid $PTRS:$ 

\begin{align*}
[PTRS] &= [PQRS] - [PQR] \\
&= PQ \times SR - \frac{1}{2}PQ \times QR \\
&= 2\sqrt{6} \times 2\sqrt{6} - \frac{1}{2}\cdot 2\sqrt{6} \cdot 2\sqrt{6} \\
&= 24 - 12 \\
&= \boxed{12}.
\end{align*}

